  "abstract": "This article deals with microbial inoculants of\r\nN,-fixing bacteria, vesicular arbuscuJar\r\nmycorrhiwe (VAM), phosphate solubilizers and \r\nplant-growth promoting rhizobacteria (PGPR) and\r\nThey, role in production of crops. Factors\r\ndetermining the success of inoculants  technology\r\nalong with a survey on their field performance are\r\ndiscussed. The rhizobial inoculants are deals in\r\ngreater detail as a general example, and for the\r\nether inoculants the discussion is restricted 10 the\r\npoints which are specific to a particular group of\r\ninoculants. To popularize biofertilizers amongst\r\nfarmers a holistic approach covering production of\r\nquality inoculants, selecting areas which need\r\ninoculationi, raining and educating extensionl staff\r\n. and appropriate crop management practices is\r\nsuggested\r\n",
